<i>Takuya Kimura and ARASHI
are very popular in Taiwan.</i>

87
00:06:24,951 --> 00:06:31,691
<i>Newer Johnny's groups are less recognized.</i>

88
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:35,528
<i>It's time for them to change that.</i>

89
00:06:38,297 --> 00:06:39,232
{\an8}SANLIH E-TELEVISION

90
00:06:39,298 --> 00:06:44,237
{\an8}<i>The next event is perfect
for showcasing Kisumai's strengths.</i>

91
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:52,545
<i>It's a very popular dance reality show.</i>

92
00:06:54,447 --> 00:06:57,884
<i>I'm going to tweak your choreography</i>

93
00:06:57,950 --> 00:07:01,621
<i>to make it cuter.</i>

94
00:07:27,647 --> 00:07:29,816
{\an8}LOCAL TV CREW

95
00:07:30,850 --> 00:07:32,885
<i>Who was the most popular?</i>

96
00:07:36,055 --> 00:07:39,525
<i>I love you.</i>

97
00:07:39,592 --> 00:07:41,594
<i>You were the most popular.</i>

98
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:44,997
It's our chance to win overseas fans.

99
00:07:46,399 --> 00:07:47,767
This is so fun.

100
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:56,142
<i>Kisumai arrives to check their stage.</i>

101
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:05,751
<i>The size of the stage is
of great importance.</i>

102
00:08:09,856 --> 00:08:13,960
{\an8}<i>Tonight's stage is inside
a special 100-meter long dome.</i>

103
00:08:16,896 --> 00:08:20,833
<i>This event is a combination
of fashion shows and musical performances.</i>

104
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:26,205
<i>Kisumai must perform
their songs on a catwalk.</i>

105
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:32,512
What is this place? It's amazing.

106
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:35,948
It's like we're in a cloud.

107
00:08:39,552 --> 00:08:41,954
<i>They immediately put on
their roller skates</i>

108
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:44,824
<i>to test the catwalk.</i>

109
00:08:46,959 --> 00:08:50,563
{\an8}REHEARSAL

110
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:54,166
{\an8}<i>The catwalk is narrower than they thought.</i>

111
00:09:00,673 --> 00:09:03,276
<i>The stage at the end
of the catwalk is also small,</i>

112
00:09:03,342 --> 00:09:07,313
<i>but Kitayama wanted
to show a stage full of speed.</i>

113
00:09:08,614 --> 00:09:11,083
Next is "Come on, Come on. Everybody go!"

114
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:21,394
<i>The dress rehearsals reveal
that they can barely pass each other by.</i>

115
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:31,103
It's different from what we're used to.

116
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:35,308
It's tight up there with our skates on.

117
00:09:35,374 --> 00:09:38,844
I don't know if we can pick up speed.

118
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:42,515
We'll have to figure something out.

119
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:46,719
The members will work it out together.

120
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:49,956
We've got to make it happen.

121
00:09:51,023 --> 00:09:55,962
When we have our skates on,
we require lots of space.

122
00:09:58,297 --> 00:10:00,132
I wish we had double what we have.

123
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:06,038
It'll depend on
whether we can build up speed.

124
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:13,079
<i>It is the second day of their stay,
the day of the event.</i>

125
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:18,117
{\an8}<i>A press conference is held
before the event.</i>

126
00:10:21,053 --> 00:10:23,889
-<i>I am so glad to be here.
-I am so glad to be here.</i>

127
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:28,194
-<i>I'm happy to meet you.
-I'm happy to meet you. Yes.</i>

128
00:10:29,562 --> 00:10:34,333
<i>The members have decided
to use Mandarin for their greetings.</i>

129
00:10:39,071 --> 00:10:43,743
<i>The press conference is packed
with media from all across Asia.</i>

130
00:10:52,518 --> 00:10:58,491
-<i>We are Kis-My-Ft2.
-Kis-My-Ft2.</i>

131
00:10:59,892 --> 00:11:01,927
Look this way, please.

132
00:11:04,597 --> 00:11:06,232
This way, next.

133
00:11:07,767 --> 00:11:11,937
<i>Will they be able to win the hearts
of the audience filling up the dome?</i>

134
00:11:12,405 --> 00:11:14,106
<i>It is time to show their growth.</i>

135
00:11:17,643 --> 00:11:19,478
<i>The event has begun.</i>

136
00:11:27,553 --> 00:11:31,457
It definitely feels
like an overseas event in here.

137
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:34,460
The atmosphere is different from Japan.

138
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:36,228
I'm really excited to go on stage.

139
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:41,233
<i>Kisumai's turn is coming up.</i>

140
00:11:47,173 --> 00:11:51,811
<i>They will use their roller skates,
a weapon that's unique to them.</i>

141
00:11:55,147 --> 00:11:58,050
I haven't been this nervous in ages.
What's gotten into me?

142
00:12:45,397 --> 00:12:48,601
<i>Let's get this stage rocking!</i>

143
00:12:52,571 --> 00:12:56,642
<i>The members skate
along the catwalk fearlessly.</i>

144
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:04,750
<i>Even if the odds are stacked against them,
they give their all.</i>

145
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:09,755
<i>That is the teaching of the man who
bestowed their roller skates upon them.</i>

146
00:13:43,122 --> 00:13:45,758
<i>They sing five songs in a row.</i>

147
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:50,029
<i>Now, it's time to test their Mandarin.</i>

148
00:13:51,764 --> 00:13:53,799
<i>I am here to find</i>

149
00:13:53,866 --> 00:13:57,970
<i>my princess.</i>

150
00:13:59,672 --> 00:14:02,041
Hang on... I've got this.

151
00:14:02,107 --> 00:14:03,709
-I know!
-You can do this!

152
00:14:04,143 --> 00:14:06,812
<i>That's you!</i>

153
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:15,988
<i>You are my girlfriend.</i>

154
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,760
<i>Amazing! So hot!</i>

155
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:25,097
-<i>I loved the roller skates.
-The roller skates.</i>

156
00:14:26,632 --> 00:14:27,566
<i>It was incredible.</i>

157
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:31,604
<i>I'm so happy to see Johnny's perform live.</i>

158
00:14:32,137 --> 00:14:35,541
Of course, I was very nervous.

159
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:38,744
I was worried
the crowd would not be accepting of us.

160
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:41,413
But they welcomed us wholeheartedly.

161
00:14:41,780 --> 00:14:43,616
I was touched.

162
00:14:46,118 --> 00:14:49,154
<i>This is what the Taiwanese media
said about them.</i>

163
00:14:49,989 --> 00:14:53,859
<i>"The fans loved
their incredible performance."</i>

164
00:14:58,430 --> 00:15:03,869
<i>Another enormous opportunity awaits them
at the end of the year.</i>

165
00:15:10,542 --> 00:15:12,011
{\an8}NHK KOHAKU UTA GASSEN REHEARSAL

166
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,914
{\an8}<i>It is the end of 2019.</i>

167
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:17,549
{\an8}<i>Kisumai is surrounded
by the media once again.</i>

168
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:24,189
<i>Fifteen years after the group was formed
and nine years after their CD debut,</i>

169
00:15:24,256 --> 00:15:28,193
<i>Kisumai will perform on this show
for the first time.</i>

170
00:15:31,297 --> 00:15:32,665
Whoa! You're sweating so much.

171
00:15:32,731 --> 00:15:37,036
We did rehearsals for the song
and MC just a while ago.

172
00:15:37,303 --> 00:15:40,105
We'll bring our best to the stage.

173
00:15:40,172 --> 00:15:44,143
<i>What do the members think of themselves?</i>

174
00:15:48,414 --> 00:15:51,884
We're not a typical Johnny's group

175
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:56,355
where every member
looks like Prince Charming.

176
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,525
We're all a little weird.

177
00:15:59,591 --> 00:16:01,493
We're weirdos.

178
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:03,996
It's good that we're all different.

179
00:16:05,597 --> 00:16:08,334
-I'm sweating like a pig.
-You are.

180
00:16:09,668 --> 00:16:10,970
I was so nervous.

181
00:16:12,104 --> 00:16:14,606
<i>They are neither typical nor princely.</i>

182
00:16:14,673 --> 00:16:17,776
<i>They are just seven weirdos traveling
on this journey together.</i>

183
00:16:19,411 --> 00:16:22,748
{\an8}Three, two, one!

184
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:24,917
{\an8}JOHNNY'S COUNTDOWN 2019-2020

185
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:28,988
{\an8}<i>It will be ten years
since their CD debut in 2020.</i>

186
00:16:40,032 --> 00:16:44,069
{\an8}<i>The seven members lead on the front line</i>

187
00:16:44,136 --> 00:16:47,706
{\an8}<i>while still searching
for a newer version of themselves.</i>

188
00:17:00,586 --> 00:17:03,322
{\an8}-What? No way!
-You're kidding?

189
00:17:03,389 --> 00:17:04,590
{\an8}Is this for real?

190
00:17:04,823 --> 00:17:07,426
-Seriously?
-Yes!

191
00:17:07,493 --> 00:17:09,361
{\an8}THE NETHER, STAGE PLAY

192
00:17:09,428 --> 00:17:11,230
{\an8}<i>Hiromitsu Kitayama.</i>

193
00:17:16,835 --> 00:17:19,304
I want to know
that I've at least given it a shot.

194
00:17:20,239 --> 00:17:22,408
Otherwise, I wouldn't be able to stand it.

195
00:17:23,675 --> 00:17:26,211
{\an8}Yes!

196
00:17:26,278 --> 00:17:27,980
{\an8}<i>Taisuke Fujigaya.</i>

197
00:17:28,047 --> 00:17:29,081
{\an8}DON JUAN, MUSICAL

198
00:17:29,148 --> 00:17:31,250
{\an8}Thank you so much!

199
00:17:43,762 --> 00:17:46,665
<i>At the end of the run,
there were tears in his eyes.</i>

200
00:17:49,268 --> 00:17:51,136
I was scared.

201
00:17:52,171 --> 00:17:54,540
But I had faith.

202
00:17:55,774 --> 00:17:58,911
I'm glad I didn't run from this challenge.

203
00:17:59,311 --> 00:18:01,180
{\an8}STAGE PLAY
<i>MARUMARU NA HITO NO MATSURO</i>

204
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:04,650
{\an8}<i>They each tackled difficult challenges.</i>

205
00:18:07,119 --> 00:18:08,387
Yes.

206
00:18:10,389 --> 00:18:11,957
<i>Toshiya Miyata.</i>

207
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,461
You two will make a great couple.

208
00:18:16,395 --> 00:18:17,830
<i>Takashi Nikaido.</i>

209
00:18:17,896 --> 00:18:19,498
Do you really think so?

210
00:18:19,565 --> 00:18:21,867
Yeah, I do.

211
00:18:23,302 --> 00:18:24,503
Here I am!

212
00:18:25,404 --> 00:18:27,005
<i>Wataru Yokoo.</i>

213
00:18:28,407 --> 00:18:30,008
Say it again.

214
00:18:30,075 --> 00:18:31,009
Okay.

215
00:18:31,343 --> 00:18:32,511
What? Really?

216
00:18:32,578 --> 00:18:35,948
Yes. I had a busy day. I'm tired.

217
00:18:36,014 --> 00:18:37,583
<i>Kento Senga.</i>

218
00:18:38,550 --> 00:18:43,021
He's had it rough, living alone
with his brother since he turned 17.

219
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:47,759
A person like me
doesn't deserve happiness.

220
00:18:47,826 --> 00:18:50,429
-Don't be stupid.
-Come on!

221
00:18:53,098 --> 00:18:56,201
<i>Through this play,
these members pondered</i>

222
00:18:56,268 --> 00:18:59,671
<i>what it means to tackle new challenges.</i>

223
00:19:06,845 --> 00:19:10,849
I want something that I am the best at.

224
00:19:12,251 --> 00:19:14,786
To be second to none in that genre.

225
00:19:14,853 --> 00:19:17,723
If all seven members can accomplish that,

226
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:22,528
maybe we can become stars.

227
00:19:25,364 --> 00:19:29,234
That's what I believe.

228
00:19:29,635 --> 00:19:33,572
I get to do these gigs

229
00:19:33,639 --> 00:19:36,241
thanks to the other six members.

230
00:19:36,975 --> 00:19:39,511
I can't do anything alone.

231
00:19:39,945 --> 00:19:44,550
Sometimes we may not all see eye to eye.

232
00:19:44,616 --> 00:19:46,351
That happens.

233
00:19:46,752 --> 00:19:50,222
But our strength lies
in us sticking together.

234
00:19:50,289 --> 00:19:53,992
We are weak if we lose even one member.

235
00:19:54,593 --> 00:19:59,331
Maybe someday, one of us will want to

236
00:19:59,398 --> 00:20:02,134
try things on their own.

237
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:07,339
But I want us to stick together forever.

238
00:20:07,406 --> 00:20:13,845
Even when we grow old and become old men,

239
00:20:13,912 --> 00:20:16,448
I want us to stick together and be tight.

240
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,484
That's my dream.

241
00:20:20,052 --> 00:20:21,787
{\an8}You're still cooking lame food?

242
00:20:21,853 --> 00:20:27,192
{\an8}<i>Yuta Tamamori is the front man of Kisumai.</i>

243
00:20:30,596 --> 00:20:34,399
Miyu is so disappointed in you.

244
00:20:35,634 --> 00:20:37,035
I bet.

245
00:20:38,337 --> 00:20:40,372
I don't want others to do what we do.

246
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:44,776
I don't want them to go crazy
on TV shows like we do.

247
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:50,315
I want people to be shocked
by what we are capable of.

248
00:20:55,354 --> 00:20:57,022
That's my goal for us.

249
00:21:03,629 --> 00:21:07,132
{\an8}<i>Idol group, Kis-My-Ft2.</i>

250
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:15,874
{\an8}<i>They aspire to be more crowd-shocking
than any other idol groups.</i>

251
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:26,051
{\an8}<i>Their journey has just begun.</i>

252
00:21:32,624 --> 00:21:34,726
{\an8}<i>Next episode, we follow Koichi Domoto.</i>

253
00:21:34,793 --> 00:21:36,261
{\an8}KOICHI DOMOTO

254
00:21:37,229 --> 00:21:41,400
{\an8}Endless SHOCK <i>is reaching
its 20th anniversary.</i>

255
00:21:42,734 --> 00:21:47,072
<i>He has fostered this musical
as the chairman and director.</i>

256
00:21:50,876 --> 00:21:54,413
If there ever comes a time when I retire,

257
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:58,350
would the musical <i>SHOCK</i> also end with me?

258
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:01,420
If so, what have I been doing this for?

259
00:22:04,389 --> 00:22:08,393
<i>What has he been thinking
behind the spotlight all these years?</i>

